\b
\ms1 Bible Study 4 // God can make us like new people
\ip There was a group of Jewish people called Pharisees. They were very strong about God’s old law for Jewish people. They also made up a lot of their own laws and they were very strong about them too. That Pharisee mob did not like Jesus, and they tried to stop him all the time.
\ip Nicodemus was one of that Pharisee mob, but he was different. He wanted to listen to Jesus. But he knew that if he went and talked to Jesus, then his Pharisee mob would get angry with him. So Nicodemus went to Jesus at night so that Pharisee mob didn’t see him. He listened to what Jesus said, then he knew he could turn his life around and become like a new person.
\s1 God’s Word – John 3:1-10, 16-18
\p 
\v 1-2 One night, a man went to talk to Jesus. His name was Nicodemus. He was a leader of the Jewish people, and he was one of the mob called Pharisees, that were strong for the Jewish law. He said to Jesus, “Teacher, we’ve been watching you do powerful things, so now we know that God has sent you to teach us. Only somebody with God’s power can do those things.” \fig A man called Nicodemus talked to Jesus one night|src="8g Nicodemus&Jesus.tif" size="col" ref="3:1-2"\fig*
\p 
\v 3 Jesus said to him, “Listen, I am telling you straight, people have to get born again, and then they can be in God’s family.”
\p 
\v 4 Nicodemus said, “How can a big man like me get back into his mother’s body and get born again?”
\p 
\v 5 Jesus said, “Listen, I am telling you straight, if anyone wants to be in God’s family, they have to get born again God’s way. God has to make them clean, and he has to put his spirit in them.
\v 6 You see, everybody is born from a human mother, that’s how our bodies get life. But if people get born again from God’s Holy Spirit, then the Holy Spirit gives new life to their spirits too.
\p 
\v 7 I said, ‘You have to get born again.’ Don’t get shocked by that.
\v 8 You know that the wind goes wherever it wants to go. You hear the sound it makes, but you don’t know where it came from, and you don’t know where it’s going. Just like that, we don’t know how God’s spirit makes people get born again.”
\p 
\v 9 Nicodemus said, “What? How can somebody get born again from God’s spirit?”
\p 
\v 10 Jesus said, “I am shocked. You are an important teacher here in Israel, and you don’t understand what I’m saying.”
\b
\p 
\v 16 You see, God loved all of the people in the world. He loved everyone so much that he sent them his only son, his special son. God sent him to die instead of them, so that if anyone trusts him, God will not finish them up, but they will live with him for ever.
\p 
\v 17 You see, God sent his son into the world so that he can save the people of the world. He didn’t send him to judge people and do payback to them.
\p 
\v 18 If anyone believes in God’s son, then God will not say they are guilty. But if anyone does not believe in him, God has already said they are guilty. You see, they do not believe in God’s only son, his special son.
