\b
\ms1 Bible Study 5 // We can drink the water that makes us really live
\ip At the time when Jesus was here on earth, he belonged to the Jewish people. And there were other people living in that country called the Samaria people. These 2 mobs did not like each other.
\ip Even though they both believed in God they were a bit different in some ways. The Samaria mob had their special site on a mountain called Gerizim, and they showed respect to God there. The Jewish mob had their special site at the city called Jerusalem, and they showed respect to God there.
\ip But in this story, Jesus talked about a new way to show respect to God.
\s1 God’s Word – John 4:4-30, 39-42
\p 
\v 4 On their way to Galilee country, Jesus and his followers had to go through the country called Samaria.
\v 5-8 They walked a long way, then they got to a water-hole. A long time ago, their grand-father, Jacob, dug that water-hole. It was near the land that Jacob gave to his son Joseph. There was a little town called Sikar near that water-hole, so Jesus’s followers went into the town to buy some food. But Jesus was tired, so he sat down next to that water-hole and waited there.
\p In the middle of the day, a woman came from the town and got some water from that water-hole. Jesus said to her, “Can you give me a drink?”
\p 
\v 9 The woman said, “What? You are a Jew, and I belong to Samaria. So why do you ask me for a drink of water?” You see, the Jews were not friends with the Samaria people. \fig Jesus talked with a woman at the water-hole|src="C_064.tif" size="col" ref="4:9"\fig*
\p 
\v 10 Jesus said to her, “I asked you for a drink of water, but really, you should ask me for a drink. You don’t know who I am, and you don’t know about the good thing that God can give you. If you ask me, I will give you the fresh water that makes people live.”
\p 
\v 11 The woman said, “Sir, this water-hole is really deep, and you haven’t got a bucket. How are you going to get that fresh water?
\v 12 Jacob, our grand-father that lived a long time ago, he dug this water-hole for himself, and for his sons, and for all their animals. They all drank this water. Do you think you are greater than Jacob?”
\p 
\v 13 Jesus said to her, “Everyone that drinks water from this water-hole will get thirsty again.
\v 14 But if anyone drinks the water that I give them, they will never get thirsty again. That water will keep coming up inside them, like a spring of fresh water, and it will make them live for ever.”
\p 
\v 15 The woman said, “Sir, give me that water. I don’t want to get thirsty. I don’t want to have to come here all the time to get water.”
\p 
\v 16 Jesus said, “Well, go and get your husband and bring him here.”
\p 
\v 17 The woman said, “I haven’t got a husband.”
\p Jesus said to her, “That’s right. You haven’t got a husband now.
\v 18 You have had 5 different husbands, and the man you live with now is only your boyfriend. You are not married to him. Yes, it’s true, you haven’t got a husband.”
\p 
\v 19 The woman said, “Sir, you know all about me. I reckon you are one of those men that get messages from God.
\v 20 So tell me who is right, you Jewish people or us Samaria people? My people have always shown respect to God by doing ceremonies on this mountain. But you Jews say that we have to go to Jerusalem to do those ceremonies and show respect to God. Who is right?”
\p 
\v 21 Jesus said to her, “Believe me, a time is coming when it will not matter if you show respect to God, the father, here on this mountain, or in Jerusalem, or anywhere else.
\v 22 You see, you people try to show respect to God, but you don’t really know him. We Jewish people show respect to God, and we know more about him. And God said that he will use a Jewish person to save everybody.
\v 23 Yes, a time is coming when the people that belong to God will show respect to him properly. And that time is happening now. They will know the true story about God, and they will respect him with their spirits. They are the sort of people that my father is looking for, to show him respect.
\v 24 You see, God is a spirit, and the people that really respect him have to know the true story about him, and they have to respect him with their spirits.”
\p 
\v 25 The woman said to Jesus, “I know that a special man is coming. He is the man that God promised to send. He is the one called the \em Messiah\em*, or the \em Christ\em*. After he comes, he will tell us everything we need to know.”
\p 
\v 26 Jesus said to her, “I am that man. Yes, that’s me, the man you are talking to.”
\p 
\v 27 Then, at that time, Jesus’s followers came back from the town. They saw Jesus and the woman, and they got a shock. He was talking to a woman. They wanted to ask her, “What do you want?” And they wanted to ask Jesus, “Why are you talking to that woman?” But they didn’t say anything.
\p 
\v 28 The woman left her bucket next to the water-hole and went back into the town, and she said to the people there,
\v 29 “Come and see a man that told me everything I ever did. Maybe he is the Christ, the special man that God promised to send, the one that we have been waiting for.”
\v 30 The people heard what she said, and they left the town to go and see Jesus.
\b
\p 
\v 39 The people in the town heard the woman say, “He told me everything I ever did,” and a lot of them believed in Jesus.
\v 40 And so they came from the town to see Jesus, and they asked him to stay with them for a while. So he stayed there for 2 days.
\v 41 He talked to them and told them his message, and even more people believed in him.
\p 
\v 42 The town people said to the woman, “We heard what you said about this man, and we believed you. But now we listened to him ourselves, and we know for sure that he is the man that God sent into the world to save people.”
\p 
\v 43 Jesus stayed with the people there for 2 days. Then Jesus and his followers left Samaria and went north to Galilee country.
